<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11026e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11026e">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11026e"> 26(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> golden sickle / verveine chaplet (Norm)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Vell&eacute;da</b> Alors, arrachant de son front <mark>sa couronne de verveine</mark>, et prenant &agrave; sa ceinture sa <mark>faucille d&apos;or</mark>, comme si elle allait faire un sacrifice &agrave; ses dieux: / &ldquo;Je ne souillerai plus, dit-elle, ces ornements d&apos;une vestale!&rdquo; / Aussit&ocirc;t elle porte &agrave; sa gorge l&apos;instrument sacr&eacute;: le sang jaillit. Comme une moissonneuse qui a fini son ouvrage et qui s&apos;endort fatigu&eacute;e au bout du sillon, Vell&eacute;da s&apos;affaisse sur le char; la faucille d&apos;or &eacute;chappe &agrave; sa main d&eacute;faillante et sa t&ecirc;te se penche doucement sur son &eacute;paule. <br><font color="green">[Then, pulling her crown of verbena from her forehead, and taking from her waist her golden sickle, as if she were going to make a sacrifice to her gods: / &ldquo;I won&apos;t defile anymore these vestments of a vestal!&rdquo; she said / Immediately she brings the sacred instrument to her throat: the blood gushes forth. Like a harvester who has finished his work and falls into an exhausted sleep at the end of the furrow, Vell&eacute;da subsides on the chariot; the golden sickle falls from her faltering hand and her head bends gently on her shoulder.]</font> <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) II, <i>Les Martyrs</i> 82</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
